Hi, I'm Wei.

Quick correction on my earlier report.

The reporter note in the original email contained the sentence "I am not
the hook author." This is incorrect.

I am the author of cinder-capture, the hook referenced throughout the
report.

The phrasing came from a draft written by Claude Code (Opus 4.6), which I
used to help structure the technical English. I didn't catch the error
before sending.

To be clear:

- I am the author of cinder-capture.
- It is a personal companion-widget experiment, not a commercial product.
- I observed the behavioral pattern described in the report over roughly
4-5days of building and using the hook.
- I have no commercial interest in this report. I'm a semiconductor
equipment engineer in Taiwan; cinder-capture was a side project that grew
into the writeup mentioned earlier.
- I have temporarily made the cinder-capture repository private and taken
down the accompanying narrative writeup, both pending your review. Both are
reversible.

The technical substance of the original report is unchanged. Apologies for
the confusion.

Thanks,

SC Wei.

